1
00:00:11,116 --> 00:00:13,118
[rock music playing]

2
00:00:43,148 --> 00:00:46,277
CHAPTER 34:
I'M THEIR HOMEROOM TEACHER

3
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:50,364
[chuckling] The-The States?
Sounds like a nice plan.

4
00:00:50,447 --> 00:00:54,660
Fair enough, though. I heard you got
many offers from many places.

5
00:00:54,743 --> 00:00:59,456
So then, are you going to go study
at a place like Harvard or MIT?

6
00:00:59,540 --> 00:01:01,709
Or are you going to be a professor there?

7
00:01:01,792 --> 00:01:04,670
[chuckles] Uh…

8
00:01:04,753 --> 00:01:08,799
How long does something like that
usually take? A semester?

9
00:01:09,592 --> 00:01:11,343
Is it a year? I mean…

10
00:01:11,927 --> 00:01:13,470
I mean… [sighs]

11
00:01:15,472 --> 00:01:17,850
If it's something that will take long,

12
00:01:18,767 --> 00:01:23,355
I'm wondering if I won't get to see you
in my senior year.

13
00:01:25,900 --> 00:01:27,109
[sighs]

14
00:01:31,071 --> 00:01:32,948
It's late. Go home.

15
00:01:35,576 --> 00:01:36,619
Gosh.

16
00:01:37,119 --> 00:01:38,203
Get home safely, okay?

17
00:01:48,380 --> 00:01:50,674
So when will you be leaving?

18
00:01:51,383 --> 00:01:53,385
[forlorn music playing]

19
00:01:58,599 --> 00:01:59,600
[sighs]

20
00:01:59,683 --> 00:02:02,895
What do you think
about your friend's offer? Na Deul-i's?

21
00:02:03,479 --> 00:02:04,480
[sighs]

22
00:02:05,189 --> 00:02:07,316
So when you have a chance
to go to the States

23
00:02:07,399 --> 00:02:08,525
and do the research you wanna do…

24
00:02:09,151 --> 00:02:10,152
[groans]

25
00:02:11,111 --> 00:02:12,863
[inhales sharply, sighs]

26
00:02:15,366 --> 00:02:19,078
I wonder, why does he have to go
with that lady though?

27
00:02:20,412 --> 00:02:24,291
I guess she really is his girlfriend.

28
00:02:26,085 --> 00:02:27,753
[clicks tongue, sighs]

29
00:02:27,836 --> 00:02:30,255
Yeah, he's human after all.

30
00:02:30,339 --> 00:02:32,091
Of course he'd have a love life.

31
00:02:33,550 --> 00:02:35,552
[sighs]

32
00:02:35,636 --> 00:02:37,554
They'll do research together

33
00:02:38,514 --> 00:02:40,099
in the States.

34
00:02:40,808 --> 00:02:42,267
Just the two of them.

35
00:02:44,103 --> 00:02:45,479
Good for them.

36
00:02:47,147 --> 00:02:48,732
[sighs]

37
00:02:50,275 --> 00:02:51,360
Hold on a second.

38
00:02:51,443 --> 00:02:53,278
If I hadn't found that out today,

39
00:02:53,362 --> 00:02:55,322
when was he going to let us know?

40
00:02:56,323 --> 00:02:57,449
At the end of the year?

41
00:02:57,533 --> 00:03:00,119
Was he going to be like,
"Hey, I'm off to the States."

42
00:03:01,745 --> 00:03:02,913
[sighs]

43
00:03:04,873 --> 00:03:05,874
Whatever.

44
00:03:07,251 --> 00:03:09,336
He doesn't have to tell us anyway.

45
00:03:10,295 --> 00:03:14,299
Whether he leaves or he stays,
that's his life.

46
00:03:15,134 --> 00:03:17,886
[sighs] And I'm just one
of his many students.

47
00:03:28,731 --> 00:03:30,733
EPISODE 11

48
00:03:30,816 --> 00:03:32,151
[indistinct chattering]

49
00:03:36,071 --> 00:03:37,406
[students] Hello.

50
00:03:37,489 --> 00:03:38,741
[student] Hey, hi.

51
00:03:43,787 --> 00:03:45,330
Are only Choi Ji-a and Jenny missing?

52
00:03:46,081 --> 00:03:47,416
-[students] Yes.
-Yes.

53
00:03:47,499 --> 00:03:49,668
Applications
for the career experience program

54
00:03:49,752 --> 00:03:51,545
are open until the end of this week.

55
00:03:52,046 --> 00:03:53,714
Check the group chat
for the announcements,

56
00:03:53,797 --> 00:03:56,383
and if you're interested,
submit an application from to Eun Ha-su.

57
00:03:56,467 --> 00:03:57,885
[students] Okay.

58
00:03:57,968 --> 00:03:59,928
-Make sure you bring them to me.
-[Ha-su] Okay.

59
00:04:01,013 --> 00:04:03,974
-That's all.
-[students] Thank you.

60
00:04:07,227 --> 00:04:10,272
Hey, Choi Ji-a's isn't here again.
What now?

61
00:04:10,355 --> 00:04:12,900
-What if you get more demerits now?
-[sighs]

62
00:04:12,983 --> 00:04:14,985
Do you think something happened to her?

63
00:04:16,278 --> 00:04:19,031
-[Yeong-jae] Like what?
-Ugh, I don't know.

64
00:04:21,992 --> 00:04:23,077
[sighs]

65
00:04:35,923 --> 00:04:37,466
How may I help you?

66
00:04:37,549 --> 00:04:38,550
Hello, ma'am.

67
00:04:38,634 --> 00:04:40,260
My name is Yeo Eui-ju,

68
00:04:40,344 --> 00:04:42,054
-and I'm Ji-a's classmate.
-Oh.

69
00:04:42,137 --> 00:04:46,433
She wasn't in school and I was wondering
if something happened to her.

70
00:04:46,517 --> 00:04:48,185
Well, she isn't here right now.

71
00:04:48,685 --> 00:04:50,104
She's probably working.

72
00:04:51,063 --> 00:04:52,439
Ah.

73
00:04:52,523 --> 00:04:54,691
Do you know where she works by any chance?

74
00:04:54,775 --> 00:04:56,944
Where was it? [puffs air] Uh…

75
00:04:57,027 --> 00:04:59,196
I heard it was a hamburger place.

76
00:04:59,279 --> 00:05:01,198
The one at the intersection
near the hospital.

77
00:05:01,281 --> 00:05:03,492
Ah. Ah, I see.

78
00:05:04,159 --> 00:05:06,078
-Thank you so much.
-Thank you for coming by

79
00:05:06,161 --> 00:05:07,538
to see if she's okay.

80
00:05:08,413 --> 00:05:09,623
Goodbye now.

81
00:05:12,292 --> 00:05:14,878
[door opens, closes]

82
00:05:15,587 --> 00:05:16,588
Oh.

83
00:05:16,672 --> 00:05:17,881
Mr. Ga.

84
00:05:19,758 --> 00:05:21,468
Ji-a isn't here right now.

85
00:05:21,552 --> 00:05:22,928
She's out working.

86
00:05:24,263 --> 00:05:25,722
How did you get here?

87
00:05:27,224 --> 00:05:31,145
Last year I saw her write down her address
on a piece of paper.

88
00:05:32,771 --> 00:05:34,314
Why don't you go home? I'll look for her.

89
00:05:36,984 --> 00:05:38,193
No.

90
00:05:39,194 --> 00:05:41,155
I'm sick of doing demerit duty,

91
00:05:41,238 --> 00:05:42,865
and I have to see Ji-a today.

92
00:05:45,492 --> 00:05:46,952
But… [sighs]

93
00:05:54,626 --> 00:05:56,170
-[worker] Ji-a?
-Yes.

94
00:05:56,253 --> 00:05:58,338
-She doesn't work here anymore.
-Huh?

95
00:05:58,881 --> 00:06:00,048
Since when?

96
00:06:00,132 --> 00:06:02,050
Uh, two weeks ago.

97
00:06:02,134 --> 00:06:03,635
No, no, no. Three weeks ago.

98
00:06:03,719 --> 00:06:07,723
Oh, uh, do you by any chance know
where she might be right now?

99
00:06:08,724 --> 00:06:09,933
A ribs restaurant.

100
00:06:10,017 --> 00:06:12,561
I heard she works there
because they pay her a lot more.

101
00:06:12,644 --> 00:06:14,229
-Do you know the name?
-I don't.

102
00:06:14,313 --> 00:06:15,856
I didn't ask.

103
00:06:17,858 --> 00:06:19,568
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

104
00:06:23,071 --> 00:06:24,323
[sighs]

105
00:06:25,699 --> 00:06:27,701
I'll go this way,
and you can try that way.

106
00:06:27,784 --> 00:06:29,328
-Let me know if you find her.
-Okay.

107
00:06:30,454 --> 00:06:32,456
[funky pop music playing]

108
00:06:37,669 --> 00:06:39,671
[no audible dialogue]

109
00:07:03,028 --> 00:07:04,196
Oh…

110
00:07:05,906 --> 00:07:09,284
Dang. What… What's wrong with that guy?

111
00:07:10,410 --> 00:07:11,495
Come on now.

112
00:07:13,372 --> 00:07:14,581
What's the matter with you?

113
00:07:14,665 --> 00:07:15,916
Are you nuts?

114
00:07:15,999 --> 00:07:18,418
Hey, you shouldn't drink
just because they offer it to you.

115
00:07:18,502 --> 00:07:19,920
Do they even know you're a high schooler?

116
00:07:20,879 --> 00:07:22,339
They tip me for it.

117
00:07:22,422 --> 00:07:23,548
Wouldn't you do the same?

118
00:07:24,967 --> 00:07:26,927
Hey, come on. Even then…

119
00:07:27,010 --> 00:07:28,262
Ji-a?

120
00:07:28,929 --> 00:07:30,013
Ji-a.

121
00:07:30,097 --> 00:07:33,558
Yeah, we got her. It's her. [laughing]

122
00:07:33,642 --> 00:07:35,269
Today's the day, isn't it?

123
00:07:35,352 --> 00:07:36,603
Right?

124
00:07:37,562 --> 00:07:39,690
I haven't gotten paid yet, though.

125
00:07:39,773 --> 00:07:41,066
-Next time--
-"Next time"?

126
00:07:41,149 --> 00:07:42,484
[laughs]

127
00:07:42,567 --> 00:07:45,070
You told us
the exact same thing last time.

128
00:07:45,904 --> 00:07:47,698
We're not a charity group.

129
00:07:47,781 --> 00:07:49,491
Come on, what's wrong with you?

130
00:07:49,574 --> 00:07:51,868
We need to put food
on the table, all right?

131
00:07:51,952 --> 00:07:53,704
I really don't have money.

132
00:07:53,787 --> 00:07:56,498
-If you don't, then make some, huh?
-Damn.

133
00:07:56,581 --> 00:07:57,958
There's lots of places to work.

134
00:07:58,041 --> 00:08:03,839
Convenience stores, karaokes,
burger joints, bars. No?

135
00:08:04,506 --> 00:08:06,008
The way I see it, dear,

136
00:08:06,758 --> 00:08:10,512
-you're going to find the money no matter…
-Whoa, what are you doing? Stop it.

137
00:08:10,595 --> 00:08:12,222
Are you her friend?

138
00:08:12,306 --> 00:08:13,682
Well, are you?

139
00:08:13,765 --> 00:08:15,475
What? You think we're gonna
do something to her?

140
00:08:15,559 --> 00:08:16,601
We're not bad guys.

141
00:08:16,685 --> 00:08:18,562
And if you're that worried,

142
00:08:18,645 --> 00:08:20,856
you can pay off
your friend's debts for her.

143
00:08:20,939 --> 00:08:22,816
-[laughs]
-Do you have any money, friend?

144
00:08:23,608 --> 00:08:24,985
-Huh?
-Wait, we're scaring her.

145
00:08:25,068 --> 00:08:26,236
Stop it, stop it.

146
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:29,573
Well then,
how much can you pay us back today?

147
00:08:30,532 --> 00:08:32,909
I swear, I have no money.

148
00:08:32,993 --> 00:08:35,996
-Damn it, are you trying to mess with me?
-What are you doing?

149
00:08:36,079 --> 00:08:38,457
-Stop it! Let go of her!
-You shouldn't do this!

150
00:08:38,540 --> 00:08:41,209
Huh? What the… Damn.

151
00:08:42,002 --> 00:08:43,003
-Ow.
-What the heck?

152
00:08:43,086 --> 00:08:44,338
Who the hell are you?

153
00:08:45,005 --> 00:08:46,006
Well?

154
00:08:46,590 --> 00:08:48,091
I'm their homeroom teacher.

155
00:08:49,259 --> 00:08:50,427
Ah.

156
00:08:50,510 --> 00:08:52,846
-You scared me.
-Damn, you're a teacher, huh?

157
00:08:53,430 --> 00:08:54,598
This is actually better.

158
00:08:54,681 --> 00:08:57,351
Why don't you just pay off her debt
on her behalf then?

159
00:08:57,434 --> 00:08:59,311
You're the ones who did this
to her too, didn't you?

160
00:09:00,354 --> 00:09:02,022
[thug 2] We wouldn't know
anything about that.

161
00:09:02,731 --> 00:09:04,483
-Hey, teach.
-[groans]

162
00:09:04,566 --> 00:09:08,028
This girl right here
borrowed money from us, all right?

163
00:09:08,111 --> 00:09:10,989
Doesn't school teach its students
to pay back what they borrow these days?

164
00:09:11,073 --> 00:09:12,115
[thug 1] Exactly.

165
00:09:15,702 --> 00:09:16,745
How much did she borrow?

166
00:09:16,828 --> 00:09:19,247
How much, you ask? Ha.

167
00:09:19,331 --> 00:09:21,666
It was about 340.

168
00:09:22,459 --> 00:09:25,796
But now, 1,700.

169
00:09:27,714 --> 00:09:28,965
Is that all she has to pay?

170
00:09:29,049 --> 00:09:31,676
-[loan sharks laugh]
-Mr. Ga!

171
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:35,430
That's right.
Whoa, you're pretty cool, teach, hmm?

172
00:09:35,514 --> 00:09:37,182
-[thug 2] Awesome.
-[thug 1] That's right.

173
00:09:37,265 --> 00:09:39,309
-All right then, here.
-Yeah.

174
00:09:39,393 --> 00:09:41,061
Wire the money to this account.

175
00:09:41,144 --> 00:09:43,063
Can you see it? Okay?

176
00:09:43,146 --> 00:09:45,190
-[phone beeps]
-I just did.

177
00:09:45,273 --> 00:09:46,483
-[thug 1] Oh, you did?
-[thug 2] Did he?

178
00:09:46,566 --> 00:09:48,026
-[thug 1] Great. Uh-huh.
-[thug 2] Great.

179
00:09:49,444 --> 00:09:51,446
Say she's debt free
while I take a video of you.

180
00:09:53,865 --> 00:09:55,784
-On November 10th…
-Yeah.

181
00:09:55,867 --> 00:10:00,247
-…we received $1700 from Choi Ji-a.
-We did.

182
00:10:00,330 --> 00:10:04,251
Since she's debt free,
we will never contact Choi Ji-a again.

183
00:10:04,751 --> 00:10:06,378
-Happy now?
-Happy?

184
00:10:06,461 --> 00:10:07,379
[phone beeps]

185
00:10:07,462 --> 00:10:09,172
Delete her number from your phones now.

186
00:10:09,256 --> 00:10:13,051
-Okay. Choi Ji-a. "Delete number." There.
-Here.

187
00:10:13,135 --> 00:10:14,136
DELETE NUMBER

188
00:10:14,219 --> 00:10:15,637
-[thug 2] Okay?
-[thug 1] Happy now?

189
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:17,764
Stay away from her for good.

190
00:10:17,848 --> 00:10:19,683
-[chuckles] Yes, sir.
-Got it.

191
00:10:20,642 --> 00:10:22,144
It was an honor to meet you today.

192
00:10:22,227 --> 00:10:24,020
-And if you ever need to take out a loan…
-Yeah.

193
00:10:24,104 --> 00:10:25,313
…call us at this number here.

194
00:10:25,981 --> 00:10:27,274
All right?

195
00:10:27,357 --> 00:10:29,526
-The number's on the business card, okay?
-That's right.

196
00:10:30,444 --> 00:10:32,487
-We'll be waiting.
-We'll give you special treatment.

197
00:10:32,571 --> 00:10:34,239
-Bye-bye.
-We're leaving, Ji-a.

198
00:10:34,322 --> 00:10:35,740
Bye-bye.

199
00:10:43,415 --> 00:10:44,624
Mr. Ga,

200
00:10:46,084 --> 00:10:47,794
I'll pay you back for sure.

201
00:10:47,878 --> 00:10:50,505
I mean it. Even if it takes a long time.

202
00:10:50,589 --> 00:10:52,215
I'll make sure to pay you back.

203
00:10:53,467 --> 00:10:54,843
Forget it.

204
00:10:54,926 --> 00:10:57,679
You just have to stop skipping school,
and do better.

205
00:10:59,389 --> 00:11:00,390
But still…

206
00:11:00,474 --> 00:11:04,019
If you wanna pay me back,
then why don't you help a kid in need?

207
00:11:04,769 --> 00:11:06,730
Later, when you grow up or something.

208
00:11:12,527 --> 00:11:14,196
-What are you doing?
-Huh?

209
00:11:16,323 --> 00:11:17,324
Well…

210
00:11:17,407 --> 00:11:19,868
it'd be good to get a picture
of the evidence.

211
00:11:21,328 --> 00:11:23,580
You seriously love taking pictures
and videos.

212
00:11:24,706 --> 00:11:25,916
Let's go.

213
00:11:28,376 --> 00:11:30,086
-Come on.
-Okay.

214
00:11:35,675 --> 00:11:38,970
Why didn't you report them
after all this time?

215
00:11:39,721 --> 00:11:42,682
One of the shelter kids
was in a similar situation.

216
00:11:43,892 --> 00:11:46,937
She borrowed money from loan sharks
and got harassed for it.

217
00:11:47,896 --> 00:11:49,940
She reported them to the police,

218
00:11:50,023 --> 00:11:52,359
but they raided the shelter
and made a big scene.

219
00:11:53,902 --> 00:11:55,737
So she had to move out

220
00:11:55,820 --> 00:11:58,156
for causing harm
to the other shelter kids.

221
00:11:58,740 --> 00:11:59,741
Oh.

222
00:12:00,367 --> 00:12:01,660
I see now.

223
00:12:02,661 --> 00:12:05,789
So, can you work a bit less from now on?

224
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:09,626
I can't.

225
00:12:09,709 --> 00:12:10,961
I need the money.

226
00:12:11,920 --> 00:12:14,172
I have to move out of the shelter
next year,

227
00:12:14,798 --> 00:12:19,511
so I need to save at least $3000
for a deposit and rent

228
00:12:19,594 --> 00:12:20,887
just to get by.

229
00:12:22,430 --> 00:12:23,723
Oh.

230
00:12:23,807 --> 00:12:25,016
I see.

231
00:12:27,185 --> 00:12:28,728
[sighs]

232
00:12:28,812 --> 00:12:31,189
CLOUD YOUTH SHELTER

233
00:12:37,112 --> 00:12:38,446
Thank you very much.

234
00:12:39,239 --> 00:12:40,699
Mmm.

235
00:12:41,783 --> 00:12:42,784
Get home safe.

236
00:12:43,577 --> 00:12:45,537
Mmm. I'll see you at school.

237
00:12:51,459 --> 00:12:52,586
[exhales sharply]

238
00:13:00,302 --> 00:13:02,679
-Let's go.
-Okay.

239
00:13:05,056 --> 00:13:07,767
Ji-a told me she couldn't report them

240
00:13:07,851 --> 00:13:10,979
because they could go to the shelter
and make a big scene.

241
00:13:11,062 --> 00:13:13,189
[sighs]

242
00:13:13,273 --> 00:13:14,691
She was afraid.

243
00:13:16,318 --> 00:13:19,529
I didn't think you'd come
all the way here for her.

244
00:13:20,322 --> 00:13:23,742
Other teachers don't even bother
whether she comes to school or not.

245
00:13:25,619 --> 00:13:28,455
I bet you didn't come all the way here
because of demerits.

246
00:13:28,538 --> 00:13:30,123
You were worried about her.

247
00:13:34,294 --> 00:13:35,378
I'm proud of you.

248
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:40,091
[chuckles]

249
00:13:41,384 --> 00:13:44,304
Anyway, if you decide to go to the States,

250
00:13:44,387 --> 00:13:48,558
is it because, over there,
you can do what you really want?

251
00:13:50,435 --> 00:13:51,686
Well, you know,

252
00:13:52,395 --> 00:13:54,439
just like I love writing novels,

253
00:13:54,522 --> 00:13:56,650
you may have something
you really love too.

254
00:13:57,692 --> 00:13:59,361
Something…

255
00:13:59,444 --> 00:14:02,864
Something that you just can't live
without doing at all.

256
00:14:02,947 --> 00:14:05,450
I'm wondering
if that's why you would leave.

257
00:14:08,787 --> 00:14:10,413
Yes, maybe that's true.

258
00:14:11,831 --> 00:14:16,461
But whatever it is, my priority right now
is teaching you girls

259
00:14:16,544 --> 00:14:17,754
while looking after you

260
00:14:18,546 --> 00:14:20,090
and keeping an eye on all of you.

261
00:14:22,050 --> 00:14:23,301
There is nothing else.

262
00:14:29,516 --> 00:14:31,810
[peaceful music playing]

263
00:15:04,050 --> 00:15:05,093
[exhales sharply]

264
00:15:11,725 --> 00:15:12,809
[sighs]

265
00:15:13,685 --> 00:15:15,854
[tender music playing]

266
00:15:27,282 --> 00:15:31,077
CHAPTER 35:
WE'LL HELP LIKE YOU'RE FAMILY

267
00:15:33,371 --> 00:15:36,040
[students chattering]

268
00:15:44,591 --> 00:15:46,134
Girls, what's up?

269
00:15:46,217 --> 00:15:48,094
-[student] Jenny!
-I'm back.

270
00:15:48,178 --> 00:15:49,262
[students clamoring]

271
00:15:49,345 --> 00:15:53,057
It's a present for you guys. Enjoy.

272
00:15:53,141 --> 00:15:56,144
-Jenny! Hi!
-Jenny! I missed you so much.

273
00:15:56,227 --> 00:15:58,271
-I'm back. Here you go.
-Hurry, get over here.

274
00:15:58,354 --> 00:16:00,023
[gasps] Thank you.

275
00:16:00,106 --> 00:16:03,401
In Yeonnam, I had to wait in line
for an hour and a half

276
00:16:03,485 --> 00:16:04,569
just to get these cookies.

277
00:16:04,652 --> 00:16:07,280
-That looks so good.
-[chuckling]

278
00:16:07,363 --> 00:16:08,323
Thank you.

279
00:16:12,494 --> 00:16:14,287
-Thanks.
-[gasps]

280
00:16:15,955 --> 00:16:17,248
You're welcome.

281
00:16:18,249 --> 00:16:19,250
[exclaims]

282
00:16:19,334 --> 00:16:21,044
[Dan-ji] Jenny, these are to die for.

283
00:16:21,127 --> 00:16:22,712
-I know! Yum!
-Mm-hmm.

284
00:16:22,796 --> 00:16:24,506
Jenny, I saw you posted so many stories.

285
00:16:24,589 --> 00:16:26,633
They just kept popping up
one after the other.

286
00:16:26,716 --> 00:16:28,343
Went to a lot of places.

287
00:16:28,426 --> 00:16:30,887
From super early in the morning
to late at night.

288
00:16:30,970 --> 00:16:33,223
Aw. My feet hurt so much.

289
00:16:33,306 --> 00:16:35,767
Oh, I got blisters too. Want to see them?

290
00:16:35,850 --> 00:16:38,019
-Oh, um, I don't think that's necessary.
-Uh, no thanks.

291
00:16:38,102 --> 00:16:39,979
-Really.
-Mm-hmm.

292
00:16:40,063 --> 00:16:41,189
[clicks tongue] Your loss.

293
00:16:42,690 --> 00:16:45,276
-Go-ya, come eat with us.
-Mmm. [chuckles]

294
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:47,195
-Thanks. I'm okay.
-[Jenny] Have some.

295
00:16:47,278 --> 00:16:49,405
-What is it?
-[chuckling nervously]

296
00:16:49,489 --> 00:16:51,074
-Hey, why…
-Jenny.

297
00:16:51,157 --> 00:16:53,326
-[Jenny] She doesn't want it?
-[Dan-ji] Jenny. Uh…

298
00:16:53,409 --> 00:16:55,203
We'll talk in the group chat, okay?

299
00:16:55,286 --> 00:16:57,497
Oh, give us some updates
on where to go in Seoul, okay?

300
00:16:57,580 --> 00:17:00,792
-Like the Han River and…
-Of course.

301
00:17:00,875 --> 00:17:02,502
Oh, oh. Sit down.

302
00:17:02,585 --> 00:17:04,379
[students] Hello.

303
00:17:06,005 --> 00:17:07,298
Mr. Ga!

304
00:17:07,382 --> 00:17:09,717
I'm back from Seoul safe and sound.

305
00:17:10,468 --> 00:17:13,513
-How was it?
-[gasps] It was super fun.

306
00:17:14,347 --> 00:17:15,390
Mr. Ga.

307
00:17:16,766 --> 00:17:18,977
Submit your field trip report
by the end of the week, okay?

308
00:17:19,727 --> 00:17:20,979
Okay.

309
00:17:27,443 --> 00:17:28,945
Time for attendance.

310
00:17:29,028 --> 00:17:30,029
[students] Okay.

311
00:17:31,698 --> 00:17:35,493
[students cheering, applauding]

312
00:17:35,577 --> 00:17:37,745
Okay, watch closely.

313
00:17:38,913 --> 00:17:40,623
Keep your feet shoulder-width apart

314
00:17:40,707 --> 00:17:42,041
and bend your knees slightly.

315
00:17:42,959 --> 00:17:44,335
Use both hands like so

316
00:17:45,003 --> 00:17:46,379
with one on the side.

317
00:17:46,462 --> 00:17:47,630
Now if you just shoot,

318
00:17:49,173 --> 00:17:50,258
it won't go in.

319
00:17:51,467 --> 00:17:53,052
You see the rectangle up there?

320
00:17:53,136 --> 00:17:55,513
You have to aim for that when you shoot…

321
00:17:57,682 --> 00:18:00,852
[students cheering, exclaiming]

322
00:18:02,937 --> 00:18:05,106
-…and you score.
-[students laughing]

323
00:18:05,189 --> 00:18:06,524
[chuckles] Let's do it.

324
00:18:07,817 --> 00:18:08,860
Ha-su.

325
00:18:16,743 --> 00:18:19,412
-There you go.
-[students cheering, exclaiming]

326
00:18:21,456 --> 00:18:22,957
-Way to go!
-Good job!

327
00:18:23,041 --> 00:18:24,250
That was so good.

328
00:18:27,003 --> 00:18:28,421
-[student 1 laughs]
-[student 2] She missed.

329
00:18:29,923 --> 00:18:31,716
Oh, my… [grunts]

330
00:18:31,799 --> 00:18:33,801
-[Gi-jeon] You're silly.
-I'm sorry. [chuckles]

331
00:18:33,885 --> 00:18:35,303
Go-ya.

332
00:18:36,679 --> 00:18:38,222
Don't mess around.

333
00:18:38,306 --> 00:18:40,391
[student laughs] This is crazy.

334
00:18:41,392 --> 00:18:42,644
Oh, wait. Wait.

335
00:18:42,727 --> 00:18:44,187
You have to use one hand, one hand.

336
00:18:44,938 --> 00:18:45,980
Like this.

337
00:18:46,606 --> 00:18:50,568
G-Go-ya's right wrist
is a little bit weak. It's fragile.

338
00:18:51,611 --> 00:18:53,947
So she sprains it often, that's all.

339
00:18:55,531 --> 00:18:56,616
Really?

340
00:18:59,077 --> 00:19:00,453
It's fine. I'll do it.

341
00:19:10,922 --> 00:19:12,298
[Gi-jeon] You can take a break.

342
00:19:13,341 --> 00:19:15,259
Did something happen between you two?

343
00:19:16,552 --> 00:19:18,513
No. Why?

344
00:19:19,347 --> 00:19:21,432
The whole vibe is different from usual.

345
00:19:22,308 --> 00:19:23,810
You aren't smiling.

346
00:19:24,394 --> 00:19:25,478
Go-ya's…

347
00:19:26,187 --> 00:19:28,231
just not feeling good. That's all.

348
00:19:28,314 --> 00:19:29,649
-[Jenny] Ah.
-[Eui-ju chuckles]

349
00:19:30,316 --> 00:19:31,859
[inhales sharply]

350
00:19:34,153 --> 00:19:36,489
Something definitely happened.

351
00:19:37,365 --> 00:19:39,826
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

352
00:19:54,340 --> 00:19:55,550
[shutter clicking]

353
00:20:03,516 --> 00:20:04,809
Whoa.

354
00:20:07,979 --> 00:20:10,398
Crazy. Ji-a's actually rich.

355
00:20:10,481 --> 00:20:13,192
Some fancy-looking people
are escorting Ji-a in a car.

356
00:20:13,276 --> 00:20:14,318
[gasps]

357
00:20:14,402 --> 00:20:15,528
Whoa.

358
00:20:15,611 --> 00:20:19,741
Crazy. Crazy, crazy, crazy, crazy, crazy.

359
00:20:19,824 --> 00:20:21,993
-[urgent music playing]
-[panting]

360
00:20:30,001 --> 00:20:32,128
Oh! Mr. Ga! Mr. Ga, what do we do?

361
00:20:32,211 --> 00:20:34,338
It's Ji-a. I think those men
from yesterday got her.

362
00:20:34,422 --> 00:20:36,382
-What are you talking about?
-Look. Jenny saw them.

363
00:20:36,466 --> 00:20:40,053
Two men put Ji-a in this car and left.
What do we do? [panting]

364
00:20:40,136 --> 00:20:42,930
-Stay right here. I'll go find her.
-Okay. Wait, huh?

365
00:20:43,014 --> 00:20:44,390
Send me a picture of their car

366
00:20:44,474 --> 00:20:45,892
-and one of their business card.
-Okay.

367
00:20:50,021 --> 00:20:52,231
[groans] Oh, what do I do?

368
00:20:52,315 --> 00:20:54,692
What do I do? What do I do?
Think, Eui-ju, think.

369
00:20:55,651 --> 00:20:58,446
[gasps] Mr. Jung.
That's right. Mr. Jung. Mr. Jung.

370
00:20:58,529 --> 00:21:00,406
GOOD CONSCIENCE PAYDAY LOANS

371
00:21:12,960 --> 00:21:14,629
[thug 1] You picked it, right? Huh?

372
00:21:14,712 --> 00:21:15,963
WE'LL HELP LIKE YOU'RE FAMILY

373
00:21:16,047 --> 00:21:18,382
Run Course C three times
and that's a thousand bucks, got it?

374
00:21:18,466 --> 00:21:20,343
-Huh?
-Choi Ji-a.

375
00:21:21,219 --> 00:21:22,428
-Uh…
-Mr. Ga!

376
00:21:22,512 --> 00:21:24,430
No, no, no, no, no. Sit back down.

377
00:21:25,056 --> 00:21:27,558
-[whimpering]
-Holy cow.

378
00:21:28,476 --> 00:21:30,561
Didn't I tell you to stay away from her?

379
00:21:30,645 --> 00:21:32,438
The teacher came all the way here.

380
00:21:32,522 --> 00:21:33,648
[chuckles]

381
00:21:34,524 --> 00:21:36,109
[boss] And who is this?

382
00:21:37,568 --> 00:21:39,362
[thug 1] Oh, her homeroom teacher.

383
00:21:40,863 --> 00:21:42,740
Well, well.

384
00:21:42,824 --> 00:21:47,286
-A teacher's kindness is sky high, huh?
-[laughing]

385
00:21:47,370 --> 00:21:49,413
[thug 2]
Look, we're really sorry about this.

386
00:21:49,497 --> 00:21:52,041
But we did the math,
and it just didn't add up.

387
00:21:52,667 --> 00:21:53,876
Prices have gone up lately.

388
00:21:55,419 --> 00:21:57,046
You know what I mean, right?

389
00:21:57,130 --> 00:21:59,674
So we just had no other choice… [inhales]

390
00:21:59,757 --> 00:22:02,135
-…but to change our interest rates.
-[thug 1] Uh-huh.

391
00:22:02,218 --> 00:22:04,095
It used to be 20% a month,

392
00:22:04,178 --> 00:22:06,389
but we had to switch it to a weekly rate.

393
00:22:07,140 --> 00:22:10,768
While our dear Ji-a wasn't paying,
the interest rate just… [exclaims]

394
00:22:11,477 --> 00:22:12,478
…skyrocketed.

395
00:22:15,731 --> 00:22:18,568
So she's got about $1,700 left to pay.

396
00:22:18,651 --> 00:22:20,153
I already paid it all off.

397
00:22:20,236 --> 00:22:22,572
Mr. Ga, don't listen
to these people, please.

398
00:22:22,655 --> 00:22:23,823
Shut the hell up!

399
00:22:24,323 --> 00:22:25,324
Be quiet!

400
00:22:25,408 --> 00:22:27,201
Anyway, this is how it is, teacher.

401
00:22:27,285 --> 00:22:30,913
If Ji-a can't pay, we'll have no choice
but to have her work part-time

402
00:22:30,997 --> 00:22:34,125
at a nice place
with very pretty ladies, you know?

403
00:22:34,208 --> 00:22:35,418
-Wait, wait.
-Mr. Ga,

404
00:22:35,501 --> 00:22:37,420
don't give any more money to these people.

405
00:22:37,503 --> 00:22:39,046
I'm okay. Don't worry about me
and get out of here.

406
00:22:39,130 --> 00:22:40,631
[metal bats clanging]

407
00:22:43,426 --> 00:22:44,427
Do you have a contract?

408
00:22:46,095 --> 00:22:47,763
Show me the contract she signed.

409
00:22:47,847 --> 00:22:49,765
With those exact terms.
Go on, let's see it.

410
00:22:51,434 --> 00:22:52,518
Huh?

411
00:22:53,352 --> 00:22:55,271
Without it, what's all this based on, huh?

412
00:22:56,981 --> 00:22:58,691
[sighs]

413
00:22:59,567 --> 00:23:00,568
[clicks tongue]

414
00:23:00,651 --> 00:23:02,653
I've had a enough of you already.

415
00:23:04,071 --> 00:23:05,990
This place isn't a teacher's office, okay?

416
00:23:06,073 --> 00:23:08,117
-[grunts]
-[Ji-a gasps]

417
00:23:08,201 --> 00:23:09,202
Mr. Ga!

418
00:23:10,286 --> 00:23:11,787
[thug 1] Goodness!

419
00:23:11,871 --> 00:23:14,665
-[laughing]
-What's the matter with you? Huh?

420
00:23:17,251 --> 00:23:19,420
I guess you guys
haven't figured me out yet.

421
00:23:22,840 --> 00:23:25,134
-[thugs chuckling]
-[thug 1] Seriously?

422
00:23:26,719 --> 00:23:28,721
[intrepid music playing]

423
00:23:37,313 --> 00:23:39,315
[tires squeal]

424
00:23:40,816 --> 00:23:42,443
PAYDAY LOANS

425
00:23:48,616 --> 00:23:49,742
This must be it.

426
00:23:50,368 --> 00:23:52,620
Eui-ju, you better wait here.
We'll come back out with them.

427
00:23:53,204 --> 00:23:55,206
-But still, I…
-Wait there.

428
00:23:55,289 --> 00:23:56,290
Won't take long.

429
00:24:15,309 --> 00:24:16,936
[boss] You like jjajangmyeon that much?

430
00:24:17,019 --> 00:24:18,229
-[grunting]
-Yes, boss.

431
00:24:18,312 --> 00:24:20,356
[boss] Look at how much you like it, huh.
Is it good?

432
00:24:20,439 --> 00:24:21,816
[laughing]

433
00:24:27,488 --> 00:24:30,449
[Eui-ju] Mr. Ga! Are you okay?

434
00:24:30,533 --> 00:24:32,326
-[groans]
-Oh, no. Are you okay?

435
00:24:32,410 --> 00:24:33,661
Oh, I'm sorry.

436
00:24:33,744 --> 00:24:34,829
Oh, my. Mr. Ga.

437
00:24:36,038 --> 00:24:38,165
What are these beautiful angels
doing here?

438
00:24:38,916 --> 00:24:42,920
What brings such a divine presence
to this humble place?

439
00:24:43,462 --> 00:24:44,463
Did you do that

440
00:24:45,923 --> 00:24:46,966
to our boy right there?

441
00:24:47,633 --> 00:24:49,218
-[laughing]
-Yeah.

442
00:24:49,802 --> 00:24:51,137
[boss] Well, now.

443
00:24:51,220 --> 00:24:53,347
[Eui-ju] Oh, my goodness, Mr. Ga.

444
00:24:53,431 --> 00:24:55,224
[Eui-ju crying]

445
00:25:02,773 --> 00:25:04,442
[rock music playing]
